## Automatic Sorting

Members are automatically sorted by position hierarchy:

1. **Mayor / Reeve** (first)
2. **Deputy Mayor / Deputy Reeve**
3. **Other positions** (councillors, etc.)

```svelte
<!-- These will be sorted automatically: Mayor first -->
<CouncilSidebar
  councilName="Council"
  members={[
    { name: 'Alice', position: 'Councillor' },
    { name: 'Bob', position: 'Mayor' },
    { name: 'Carol', position: 'Deputy Mayor' }
  ]}
/>
```

## Member Interface

```typescript
interface CouncilMember {
  name: string;
  position?: string;  // Mayor, Deputy Mayor, Councillor, etc.
  ward?: string;      // Ward 1, Ward 2, etc.
}
```

## Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `councilName` | `string` | required | Name of the council |
| `members` | `CouncilMember[]` | `[]` | Array of council members |

## Features

- **Auto sorting**: Mayor/Reeve always first, Deputy second
- **Position display**: Shows position in primary color
- **Ward display**: Shows ward in secondary text
- **Card wrapper**: Uses Card component for consistent styling
- **Empty handling**: Shows message when no members provided
